[
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(15) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "As the Father knoweth me, even so know I the Father.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—Better, . . . ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "and I know the Father.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " Our version, by its rendering, and by the division of verses, fails to give the full meaning, and there is thus, indeed, no reason for the assertion of the mutual knowledge of the Father and the Son. But connecting the words with those of the previous verse, we have, “I am the Good Shepherd, and know ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "those who are Mine, and those who are Mine know Me, even as the Father knoweth Me, and I know the Father.”",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " This deeper sense of union between the human spirit and Himself, and the wondrous likening of it to the union of Himself and the Father, is present to His mind as the close of His work on earth draws near. We find it again in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 14:20",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 15:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 17:8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 17:21",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". It is bound up with the thought of the love which lays down His own life for them. This is repeated here and again in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 10:17-18",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Henry's Concise Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "10:10-18 Christ is a good Shepherd; many who were not thieves, yet were careless in their duty, and by their neglect the flock was much hurt. Bad principles are the root of bad practices. The Lord Jesus knows whom he has chosen, and is sure of them; they also know whom they have trusted, and are sure of Him. See here the grace of Christ; since none could demand his life of him, he laid it down of himself for our redemption. He offered himself to be the Saviour; Lo, I come. And the necessity of our case calling for it, he offered himself for the Sacrifice. He was both the offerer and the offering, so that his laying down his life was his offering up himself. From hence it is plain, that he died in the place and stead of men; to obtain their being set free from the punishment of sin, to obtain the pardon of their sin; and that his death should obtain that pardon. Our Lord laid not his life down for his doctrine, but for his sheep.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Barnes' Notes on the Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "As the Father knoweth me ... - See the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 11:27",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " note; also ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Luke 10:22",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " note.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "I lay down my life for the sheep - That is, I give my life as an atoning sacrifice for their sins. I die in their place, to redeem them from sin, and danger, and death. See John 10:17-18. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "I lay down my life for the sheep - That is, I give my life as an atoning sacrifice for their sins. I die in their place, to redeem them from sin, and danger, and death. See ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "John 10:17-18",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
