  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Expositor's Greek Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 10:15",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". This reciprocal knowledge is so sure and profound that it can only be compared to the mutual knowledge of the Father and the Son: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "καθὼς",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " … ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "πατέρα",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". He then applies to Himself what had been stated in general of all good shepherds in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 10:11",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 10:16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " might suitably have begun with the words “And my life I lay down for the sheep”. This statement is, however, prompted by His reference to His knowledge of the Father. He knows it is the Father’s will that He should lay down His life. See ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 10:17-18",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Cambridge Bible for Schools and Colleges",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "15",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "As the Father knoweth me, even so",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
