  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Bengel's Gnomen",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 10:15",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "Καθώς",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "as",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") This is connected with the preceding verse. Often the relation of believers towards Christ is derived from the peculiar relation of Christ towards the Father: ch. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 14:20",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", “I am in My Father, and ye in Me, and I in you;” ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 15:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", “If ye keep My commandments, ye shall abide in My love, even as I have kept My Father’s commandments and abide in His love; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 17:8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 17:21",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", “I have given unto them the words which Thou gavest Me;—That they all may be one, as Thou, Father, art in Me, and I in Thee, that they also may be one in us;” ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Matthew 11:27",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", “Neither knoweth any man the Father, save the Son, and he to whomsoever the Son will reveal Him;” ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Luke 22:29",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", “I appoint unto you a kingdom, as My Father hath appointed unto Me;” ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Corinthians 11:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", “The Head of every man is Christ,—and the Head of Christ is God;” ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Corinthians 15:28",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", “The Son also Himself shall be subject unto Him that put all things under Him, that God may be all in all;” ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Revelation 3:21",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", “To him that overcometh will I grant to sit with Me on My throne, even as I also overcame, and am set down with My Father on His throne.”—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "καί",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "and",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " for that reason [viz. because ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "I am the Good Shepherd",
        "children": []
      },
      {
